President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Roslyn A. Mazer as Inspector General for the Department of Homeland Security. Mazer is currently the Inspector General of the Office of the Director of National Intelligence and has extensive experience in senior positions at the Department of Justice. She holds a B.A. from Syracuse University and a J.D. from the Columbus School of Law.

President Obama has also announced his intent to appoint Gabriel Guerra-Mondragon as a member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board. Guerra-Mondragon is the President of his own international consulting firm and previously served as the United States Ambassador to Chile. He has a bachelor's degree from Fordham University, a Master of Arts from the School of Advanced International Studies, and a law degree from the University of Puerto Rico Law School.

Additionally, Dallin Jensen will be appointed as a member of the Utah Reclamation Mitigation and Conservation Commission. Jensen is a water law attorney at Parsons Behle & Latimer and has previously served as Assistant Utah Attorney General and Utah Solicitor General. He holds a J.D. from the University of Utah and a B.S. in geology from Brigham Young University.